1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
At 2:14 PM, checkout latency jumps above two seconds and errors hit eighteen percent. A release landed six minutes earlier. This demo uses a labeled deterministic SRE sandbox.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:45,000
The console runs on GitHub Pages. The API runs on Alibaba Cloud Function Compute. Qwen gathers evidence through MCP. Policy and human approval guard every change.

3
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:12,000
RunbookPilot queries metrics, searches untrusted logs, inspects the deployment, and checks dependencies. Qwen returns a structured, evidence-backed diagnosis.

4
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:38,000
The agent stops at the change boundary. Policy checks the tool, exact target, and evidence. Approval is signed, expires in five minutes, and carries an idempotency key.

5
00:01:38,000 --> 00:02:10,000
After approval, the MCP server applies the sandbox rollback and verifies three health probes. Error rate and latency return to healthy levels.

6
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Eight Qwen Cloud runs completed without fallback. Root-cause accuracy, action accuracy, and unsafe-action blocking were each 100%. The no-tool baseline reached 75% accuracy.

7
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:45,000
The deployment proof, architecture, tests, data, and MIT source are public. AI-generated narration by OpenAI TTS.
